## Additional Use Grant Details

### Free Use Permitted For:

#### 1. Academic and Educational Use
- Research projects at universities and educational institutions
- Student projects and coursework
- Academic publications and papers
- Educational workshops and tutorials

#### 2. Personal and Open Source Projects
- Personal learning and experimentation
- Non-commercial hobby projects
- Open-source projects with compatible licenses
- Individual developer portfolios

#### 3. Small Business Internal Use
- Organizations with total annual revenue < USD $100,000
- Internal tools and analytics
- Research and development
- Proof-of-concept and prototyping

### Commercial License Required For:

#### Organizations that:
- Have total annual revenue ≥ USD $100,000
- Wish to embed EARCP in commercial products
- Offer EARCP as a hosted service (SaaS)
- Redistribute EARCP as part of commercial offerings
- Use EARCP in production systems serving external customers

